We ascribe beauty to that which is simple; which has no superfluous parts; which exactly answers its end; which stands related to all things; which is the mean of many extremes.  ~Ralph Waldo Emerson

Confucius once said that everything has beauty, but not everyone sees it. alas it is prom time, a time for girls to go over board on dresses, hair, and makeup, and boys to plot there oh so consiquencial nite. Who will be in their group? Where will pictures be? What time will we leave? When does the limo come? What will we do after? Ah... doesnt sound fun to me, and yet, I have been prodded into attending this cliche bathetic spiel. PEople thinking im some sort of grisette are wrong, i like to have a good time, not with school kids, with chaperones, and a pathetic date who thinks he knows all the moves to N'SYNC's bye bye bye video.  But Im pretty sure i will be attending, with some boy i dont know, who is said to be...ah yes...shorter than all  5 feet 9 inches of me. and to add to it, its my half birthday...the best part of the entire deal...leaving early and going to a concert downtown.
most people would call they're prom night, a night to remember....
hopefully i can forget.
....priceless

I say to mankind, Be not curious about God.  For I, who am curious about each, am not curious about God - I hear and behold God in every object, yet understand God not in the least.  ~Walt Whitman, Leaves of Grass

I have returned from KAIROS. ah the uncertainty of it all. what an eye opening expirience for me, not souly fun, not souly soul. I am so happy i went, i truly believe i have come out a different person and i really want others to consider going also....My marist girls i met were so adorable, I <3 a bunch of them..and the other girls i met from marian were awesome, they were all so beautiful, and helped me so much. Each girl was such an inspiration and i thank them all for what they gave me. i can never say i feel alone anymore, because i have kairos105 with me when ever i need them. Kairos isnt just Gods time, it was my time. time for me to find me, and love me. i reflected on past expiriences, choices, bad decisions, and have come to be at peace with myself and God. this doesnt make you a jesus freak honestly if you go. i am still the same amy, just improved. i have learned alot about myself, including the fact that i run away from relationships with my friends, God, family, and especially guys because i dont want to expirience rejection or  pain, but i have learned that i do want some meaningful relationships with all of the above. i no longer fear to put myselt completely out there, i want those relationships that i've always pushed away...including trying to have meaningful ones with...guys...i know i said it... me right? amy wants to have more than a one night thing? i know...hard to believe, but true. but if i never go out the extra mile, how will i find what im looking for? OH OH OH AND I HAVE TO TELL YOU! a marist girl brought her guitar and the first day...i played for a bunch of girls...it was AWESOME. they were so supportive of me and my music, and they loved it. it made me feel so talented, even if my chords arent the toughest, and the lyrics arent the deepist, it touched them that i just played and sang my own things, and i loved it. i truly do want to pursue music in my future. It defines a large part of who i am. AWA2IG2AC
AIAOYIFTRALY
Amy

Every man alone is sincere.  At the entrance of a second person, hypocrisy begins.  We parry and fend the approach of our fellow-man by compliments, by gossip, by amusements, by affairs.  We cover up our thought from him under a hundred folds.  Ralph Waldo Emerson, "Friendship," Essays, 1841


ugh im so sick of where i am right now its not even funny. stuck at school with mostly people i dont like, taking classes i dont care about, worrying about the rest of my life when all i can think about is being somewhere else. i wish the rest of highschool would fly by and i could be anywhere but here. the chaotic world of a 17 year old catholic school girl may sound trivial, thus the problems arise.  looking cute, being thin, nice clothes, they all add up to one misinterpretation of lots of us...that is superficial rich kids, not the case at all. I love how people think i have no pressure...right...try having a perfect sister, and dont think im saying it sucks, i love her more than anything in the world, but its hard to live up to such high expectations around here. im not as smart as her and i have no control of my insane temper, and im not afriad of their disapproval. It also blows when you dont have too many "real" friends. because in the marian world, its every girl for themself...including the people you thought would never waver, seeing as you never did. i figure if i could just move on from here i could be in less of a pergitorial state.  frustration frustration. 

shower time...until next time

Life is a shipwreck but we must not forget to sing in the lifeboats.-Voltaire

i had alot of fun this weekend with my sister at her school...we danced danced danced the night away...it was tons-o-fun. i got to play two new songs for her and i think she really liked them... 

katrin and i composed a list of my best songs...there are 22, we cut out alot of the old or redundant ones, and ended up with 22...22...thats about 22 more than most people i know, but noone ever hears them, aside from the usual crew, and passerby that hears the chorus of aria. as i sit in my bedroom, with the door locked, pick in hand, cappo on fret, words on paper, chords in motion i soon feel home. i know that sounds indecorous but its the utmost example of the truth. to some, other people make them feel whole, or found, like one of my songs, but all i need is my music and im right where i want to be.  i dont exactly know if that is good ...or...impaired..is it bad that i dont feel like i need anyone but myself? of course i would die without my sister, and my parents and i would hate not to have friends...but when it boils down to it, i love music. not more than these people in the least, but enough so where i never feel alone, and any feeling i encounter, just goes into a song. i love recalling exactly what i was feeling and exactly what happened to evoke such a mellody, or striking phrase in a composition.  i love how people hear my songs and can apply their own meaning to it, or relate it to someone in there lives. i wish i could share it with more people but i have this accute fear of rejection when it comes to my music...i kno me right...scared of what other people think? i just donno 

well another day another dollar...and im rich with things to say

The future has a way of arriving unannounced.  ~George F. Will

and it has. im going to be 17 in like 3 weeks, but i've come to question what i have accomplished and wondered....am i a quitter,? i quit softball and volleyball, trying in school, at work...

and to think that this year, i have to essentially decide the rest of my life scares me out of my mind...i dont like worrying about tomorrow led alone my entire future... there are so many things i want to do...but everything involves guts...and courage is one department i am lacking...i have so many qualms about it all... how are you supposed to just chose one thing, when there are so many things that i want to do... i want to go to school on the east coast and be independent, i want to start my own magazine, publish a book, have my own gallery, put my music out there and not be so afraid of what people think...i want to have my own fashion line, andlive abroad in paris, or milan, or venice, or dublin...i want to move to chicago and live with my sister, i want to try acting, and writing screenplays, i want to do it all, but the real question is...can i do any of it? 

and the first step...is picking a college
what shall i do...emily dickenson once said ....
That it will never come again Is what makes life so sweet.
...i say...
very true..but its filled with a whole bunch of crap
untill next time...

as i talk to louise i am reminded of the everso churning rumor mill that coincides with the homecoming season... girls go over board on dresses and make up, over plan and underestimate how  wrong things will go, and end up going with some guy they dont even like just so they can go all gussied up to a school gym...typical highschool drama...

i have made up my mind. i am skipping the highschool drama and growing up, quite the opposite of my idol peter pans philosophy, ii have decided that its not that i do not fit with highschool, highschool doesnt fit with me.

i have to go watch videos of my as a retarded 2 year old who still cannot speak ...at all just makes wierd noises owell...

everything must start somewhere...this is where i begin.
my sister Linds is coming home this weekend, actually i am going to get her tomorrow shes not coming...im going...it should be fun, im excited, i hope she is too, i mean its not as exciting as going to see her beloved (as i have just found out) brian but what can ya do. anything will be better than last weekend...long story short, sitting on some roof playing with my retainor (which does resemble a clingon warship)(sorry to all you trekies i know i spelled klingon wrong...dont kill me) would have been funner...and funner isnt a word but hey i had a bad weekend so cut me some slack.  

one more day of school tho before than,... whoever said highschool was the best time of your life was incalculably mistaken.  i don't know about you but i think these pubescent years just make you want to grow up faster. its like your lungs are ready but you still cant breathe....and it bites. i can drive, and have a boyfriend, and go out to parties, but i have to be home by 11:45...it just doesnt make any sense. its purgatory, halfway there, but still incapable of autonomy. i dont kno... i just dont

my sister has a significant other at the moment... i never got that significant-major, noteworthy...other-person? so this really means noteworthy person?...im a noteworthy person...do i recieve this title? no its so close and yet so very far away...
i do not have a significant other...i have many noteworthy people in my life, but not one above all else... 
ah yes just one more thing to write a song about.

i leave you with a question...
so when its winter here its summer in australia, so is there summer break in december? so if you move there are you one grade higher? wait...do they even go to school there? WHO KNOWS?

jusqu'au temps prochain au revoir!
Ami
